COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
State of Oklahoma
SPEAKER:
CHAIR:
I move to amend SB2060
Of the printed Bill
Page Section Lines
Of the Engrossed Bill
On page 7, line 10 1/2 by adding the following language:
"4. Nothing in the improvement plan interferes with a city or county’s
ability to protect infrastructure, comprehensive planning, zoning or any
other requirements the city or county shall impose through contracts
between the governing bodies and the applicant of the proposed Master
Development District."; and
On page 17, line 21 1/2, by inserting a new Section 6 to read as follows:
SECTION __. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified in the
Oklahoma Statutes as Section 39-122 of Title 11, unless there is created a
duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Nothing in this act shall be construed to authorize districts to provide
electric or natural gas service, construct or own electric or natural gas
utility facilities, contract for or receive electric or natural gas
service from a party which is not authorized to provide retail electric or
natural gas service in this state, impair the rights or property of a
certificated electric or natural gas utility, or limit the jurisdiction of
the Oklahoma Corporation Commission without the utility’s consent." ;
and by renumbering subsequent sections
AMEND TITLE TO CONFORM TO AMENDMENTS
